        "favorite_text": "18",
        "caption_text": "🐦‍⬛ Crow pose is a combination of balance, coordination, core engagement, and learning how to distribute your weight with control and awareness.One of the most common mistakes in crow is trying to muscle your way into the pose. In reality, the posture becomes much more accessible when you focus on creating a strong foundation through the hands, engaging the core, and gradually shifting your center of gravity forward.It also helps develop concentration.The moment the mind becomes scattered or hesitant, the posture usually reflects it immediately.Like many arm balances, crow is less about forcing the pose and more about patience, repetition, and consistent practice.You do not need to rush the process.Build the foundation.Stay focused.Keep practicing.@Inner Dimension #yoga #armbalance #crowpose #learnyoga #yogapractice",
